704305f-c.text:
(1)
1754 Flatbush Ave., west side, at the intersection of Ave. J, and East 35th Street, showing the Stoothoff-Duryea farmhouse. Shown on the left, is a view southward on Flatbush Ave., with East 35th Street
on the right.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, a closer view.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(3)
The same, as No. 2, from a slightly different angle.
1922.

(4)

and is at the S.W. corner of East 35th Street.
March 1925.
EEugene L. Armbruster Collection.

704302f-b.text:
(1)
1754 Flatbush Ave., west side, at the intersection of Ave. J. and Tast 35th Street. This house was on the Stoothoff Farm, built by that family. It was occupied by Richard Coe in 1860, by V. K. Stephenson in 1873 and by the Amersfort Nursery in 1922, when it was owned by John B. Lott. Since 1922, this house has been moved, though its present location is unknown.
1922.
Eugene L Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, another view.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(3)
The same, another angle.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
